---
description: Next.js App Router best practices
globs: ["src/app/**/*.ts", "src/app/**/*.tsx", "proxy.ts", "next.config.ts"]
alwaysApply: false
---

Next.js rules:

- Use App Router conventions.
- Use typed `Metadata` for static metadata when possible.
- Prefer Server Components for data loading.
- Add `"use client"` only for interactivity, stateful hooks, or browser-only APIs.
- Use route handlers for backend-for-frontend endpoints.
- Use `proxy.ts` for request boundary concerns like auth/session refresh, not for general app logic.
- Be deliberate with caching and revalidation.
- Avoid unnecessary dynamic rendering.
- Do not move protected logic into client components.
- Use `next/link`, `next/image`, and `next/font` where appropriate.
